This had always worked for me in the past, but as time changed and more people flaked on me or wanted me to wait beyond an agreed upon time/day, I have changed my method to a "first with the cash gets the prize". The Cons: 2nd owner so I do not know full history of rifle or round count, but the finish is, well horrible which from my understanding is common trait of Egyptian AK’s. Mechanically this rifle is in excellent condition. It will come with 2 surplus steel mags, but these both have some rough patches on the finish like there was some surface rust that was cleaned off in the past. Selling because, well it just doesn't get shot much (probably because I don’t have any 7.62x39 ammo). Can send more pics upon request.

title: For Sale:  Barrett REC7
postcontent:
The Barrett REC7 is a powerful and reliable rifle styled in the familiar AR configuration. It's a no-nonsense rifle designed to answer the call for a low-maintenance, enhanced-reliability carbine. The REC7 exceeds expectations operators demand from today's new breed of piston-operated rifles. 

The REC7 rifle's dependability stems from its innovative operating system. Using a minimum number of parts, the piston system separates heat and powder residue from the bolt carrier and trigger assembly. The rifle runs cool and clean, resulting in reduced maintenance requirements and increased endurance. 

The patented, chrome-lined, fluted gas chamber design prevents excessive carbon buildup from impairing operation under adverse conditions. This in turn allows the one-piece, 17-4 stainless piston to transfer energy to the anti-tilt bolt carrier. Machined from a monolithic block of 8620 steel, the carrier features an integral piston strike face. There is no separate gas key to shoot loose, and the nickel Teflon coating increases lubricity and simplifies cleaning. The Barrett Enhanced Piston Bolt is made from nickel Teflon coated 9310 steel. The bolt's gas ring-free design is easy to clean and operates smoothly. Reinforced at critical areas, every bolt is proofed and magnetic-particle inspected to guarantee reliable performance. 

At the heart of the system is the nitrided, two-position (suppressed/unsuppressed) gas regulator that retains the piston. The piston can be accessed through the gas block without removing the handguard, so optical sights or laser devices do not need to be re-zeroed after routine maintenance. The top of the gas block also has an integral 1913 rail, extending the rail length for mounting accessories or sights. 

The REC7 rifle's forged 7075 aluminum upper and lower receivers are type 3 hardcoat anodized. The lower houses an ultradependable, mil-spec single stage trigger. The upper supports a free-floated, 16-inch hammer forged, chrome-lined barrel with M4 feed ramps machined into both the receiver and the barrel extension. A mil-spec A2 flash hider protects the muzzle.

This had always worked for me in the past, but as time changed and more people flaked on me or wanted me to wait beyond an agreed upon time/day, I have changed my method to a "first with the cash gets the prize". Eagle Arms by Armalite AR-10 7.62/.308 
$2450 or best offer

What’s the difference between Eagle Arms and ArmaLite?
ANSWER:  There are normally very few differences.  ArmaLite rifles are the top of the company’s line.  They tend to be more up to date and include higher quality parts such as chrome lined barrels.  They are produced from selected forging.  However, internally, they use exactly the same parts.  Eagle Arms rifles are intended to compete with lower priced brands. They are extremely high quality rifles in their own right.  ArmaLite used to use only “ArmaLite” lower receivers for actual factory built guns and sold “Eagle Arms” as stripped lower and upper receivers.  This was to differentiate between the two different warranties.  ArmaLite has a lifetime warranty and EA has a one year only warranty.
